item.title: Modular Shelf - stackable and hold up to 50 pounds
item.description:
Suggested Print Setting
Support - On Buildplate Only
Infill - 25%
Layer - .28mm, really doesn't matter

This is for a series of legs to build your own shelf. In addition to printing it out, you will need a board that measure .75 inches thick, the length and width of the board is entirely up to you.

There are three shelves avaiable here

  1. the one marked s200mm are stackable and is 200 mm tall.
    -s200mm1 is used for the first story of the shelf, s200mm2 is used for the second story and up, s200mm3 is used for the final story, to cap it off. So if you only want a 2 story tall shelf, use s200mm1, and s200mm3 only

  2. The one marked s250mm are also stacable and it is 250 mm tall. The insturction is the same as the 200mm one

  3. the one that are marked ss200mm and ss250mm are single story shelf, that mean, you only want the elevated level. This one you need to use the file marked as bracket for the bottom part in order for it to be stable.

I also include a file called wall anchor in case you want to secured it to the wall. Which I highly suggested

Which ever size and version you decided, just make sure you print 4 of the same leg per story.

item.title: LETTERS - 250mm "α" and "ω" - 300x300 print plate
item.description:
3d print - LETTERS - "α" and "ω"

In order to test the parts from the 250mm letters series, download for free the "α" and "ω" letters, to print and see if you are happy with the final result.

https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/art/3d-print-letters-and-250mm

Require a 300mm X 300mm print plate!

Not a physical product ! STL and DXF format.

Stl files for letter BODY and letter FACE will be provided.

As a bonus, you will receive a dxf file of the letter FACE.

DXF file is not offset from the BODY wall, therefore, base on the laser kerf, bit tool you are using, offset accordingly!

To ensure a perfect fit, letter FACE comes with 3 offset dimensions: 0.3, 0.4 and 0.5mm. Based on you printer settings chose the one fitting your print BASE. Recommend starting with FACE 0.4mm.

All parts are check for naked edges or errors.

If you have any difficulties in printing this part, please let me know! We will try to fix it together!

Design to print without support ... :) By Costa

3D PRINTING SETTINGS
Design was made for a print using 0.4mm nozzle, 1.2mm in/out walls, 20 infill.
For prints using ABS and ASA filaments, an enclosure for your printer is strongly recommended.

item.title: Sink and Disposal Strainer
item.description:
Yet Another Sink Strainer: Keep your measuring spoons and teaspoons from going down the disposal! And keep the bulk of the food from going down -- using the disposal for anything but small scraps is notorious for clogging drain and sewer lines.

My friends wanted one or two each. I measured their sinks and found three common sizes. STL files are provided for those (3 in = 76.2 mm, 3 1/8 in = 79.4 mm, 3 1/4 in = 83.0 mm).

In addition, the OpenSCAD source file is included to allow customization. For that, open it in OpenSCAD, use the Customizer Window to modify parameters as desired using F5 to preview, and when satisfied press F6 to render followed by F7 to save as STL.

By default, the handle is decoratively faceted. It can be removed, or rounded into a sphere by increasing $fn. The curb around the outside can be raised, lowered or removed. The number of rows and columns of holes and the size of the holes are under your control.

If printed in PLA and you pour hot pasta water over it, it may sag slightly toward the middle, but it's not too bad. PLA is not harmed by water (I have a running experiment with some pieces in water and they remain unchanged after 6 months).

item.title: Banana Lamp 1.0
item.description:
This is a banana lamp I designed for fun. It could be a lovely night lamp for yourself or a surprise gift for your friends.

I modified the structure several times, and printed 5 prototypes, in order to make the light inside looks perfect, even tried the downwards LED Bulb setup. Only a small area needs support, the 4 peels legs and the center of the body. I use 0.2mm level height and 40% infill to save time, almost 19 hours in my machine to print the body.

The Bulb is LED bulb（less than 3.5W) with E12/E14 base. You can buy kinds of stuff on Amazon. See the last image for the assembly instructions.

You can also download or buy my other mushroom lamps :
Mushroom Lamp 1.0(free):
https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:5027753
